{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>A couple of years ago, my new years resolution was to stop spending lots of money on subscription services. I used to host a number of small websites for friends on WebFaction. My personal website, an ancient wordpress blog, was also hosted there, and vanished once I shut everything down. </p>\n<p>It's 2019, and I've resolved to start writing again â€“ and that means I need a website. But, I don't want to tangle with systems administration. I work at a SaaS company, there are enough servers, pipelines, environments and databases to worry about in my day job. </p>\n<p>Javascript, APIs and Markup, the <a href=\"https://jamstack.org\">JAMStack</a>, offer a great way to get a simple personal website off the ground with low ongoing maintenance. The website is compiled into static HTML, and can be served from any content delivery network. I've long been a fan of this static website + API approach, in fact I built a static site generator for a client project, dubbed <a href=\"#\">the Wrangler</a> way back in 2013. </p>\n<p>The tools to ship a static site have got much, much better over the last few years. I'm using <a href=\"#\">Gatsby</a> for this website, which uses React as its templating engine. </p>\n<h3>Gatsby articles I've found useful:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\">TODO</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#\">TODO</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#\">TODO</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>That's all for now.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"January 10, 2019","path":"/articles/building-the-new-joshbarrcom-website","title":"Building the new joshbarr.com website","blurb":"The colophon is a wonderful concept from publication design that's found its way to the internet. This is my website's colophon, giving details of its authorship and printing.","tags":["Frontend development"],"cover_image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/6d91c86c0fde632ba4cd01062fd9ccfa/33cb6/gatsby-astronaut.png","srcSet":"/static/6d91c86c0fde632ba4cd01062fd9ccfa/35833/gatsby-astronaut.png 220w,\n/static/6d91c86c0fde632ba4cd01062fd9ccfa/b6915/gatsby-astronaut.png 440w,\n/static/6d91c86c0fde632ba4cd01062fd9ccfa/33cb6/gatsby-astronaut.png 800w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}},"authors":[{"id":"josh_barr","name":"Josh Barr","image":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":40,"height":40,"src":"/static/1be02526650c5f3794fbaa03a5708f0e/f38db/josh.png","srcSet":"/static/1be02526650c5f3794fbaa03a5708f0e/f38db/josh.png 1x,\n/static/1be02526650c5f3794fbaa03a5708f0e/5d50f/josh.png 1.5x,\n/static/1be02526650c5f3794fbaa03a5708f0e/43b87/josh.png 2x,\n/static/1be02526650c5f3794fbaa03a5708f0e/495f6/josh.png 3x"}}}}]}}},"pageContext":{}}